import math.ceil
	quantity = self.view.params.Event.quantity		
	startDate = system.date.parse(self.props.value)
	duration = int(math.ceil(1.0 * self.view.params.Event.quantity/self.view.params.Event.rate))
	endDate = system.date.addHours(startDate, duration)
	params = {"ID":self.view.custom.eventDetails.eventId,
			"StartTime":startDate,
			"EndTime":endDate,
			"Quantity":quantity}
	return system.db.runNamedQuery("Scheduling/UpdateWOScheduleEntry", params)

workOrderScheduleID = self.view.custom.eventDetails.eventId
	startTime = self.view.custom.eventDetails.startDate
	
	endTime = self.view.custom.eventDetails.endDate
	system.perspective.print(self.props.data[event.row][0])
	if self.props.data[event.row][0] == "Quantity":
		qty = event.value
		dur = int(3600* system.db.runScalarPrepQuery(("Select [dbo].[getDuration](?, ?)"), [self.view.custom.eventDetails.WorkOrderID,qty]))
		lastStart = startTime
		endTime = system.date.addSeconds(lastStart, dur)
		checkDt = True
		includedDT = []
		while (checkDt):
			checkDt = False

			for item in self.view.params.DowntimeEvents:
				if int(self.view.custom.eventDetails.itemId) == int(item["itemId"]) and lastStart < item["startDate"] and endTime > item["startDate"] and item["startDate"] not in includedDT:
					includedDT.append(item["startDate"])
					dur -= system.date.secondsBetween(lastStart, item["startDate"])
					lastStart = item["endDate"]
					endTime = system.date.addSeconds(lastStart, int(dur))
					checkDt = True	
		params = {"ID":workOrderScheduleID,
			"StartTime":startTime,
			"EndTime":endTime,
			"Quantity":event.value}
		system.perspective.print(params)
		#Use Scheduling.updateSchedule to update the start and end times properly		
		result = system.db.runNamedQuery("Scheduling/UpdateWOScheduleEntry", params)
		for event in self.view.params.events:
			if event["eventId"] == self.view.params.scheduledEvent.eventId:
				event["Quantity"] = qty
		system.perspective.closePopup("")
		system.perspective.sendMessage("updatedQuantity", {})
		return result
